.TH GIT-HASPR 1 "2026-07-23" "gitplus" "gitplus Manual"
.SH NAME
git-haspr \- check whether a branch already has a pull request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git haspr
.RI [ BRANCH ]
.br
.B git haspr
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Check whether
.I BRANCH
(or the current branch, if none is given) already has a pull request, in any
state \(em open, closed, or merged \(em so it also catches a PR that already
landed or was closed, before you go create a duplicate.
.PP
If any PR exists for the branch, its URL and state are printed and the exit
status is 0. Otherwise a clear message is printed and the exit status is 1,
so it is usable in scripts:
.BR "if git haspr; then ...; fi" .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Requires the GitHub CLI
.RB ( gh ),
authenticated for the repository
.RB ( "gh auth login" ).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B git haspr
Check the current branch.
.TP
.B git haspr task/foo
Check a specific branch.
.TP
.B git haspr || gh pr create
Open a PR only if this branch doesn't already have one.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr (1),
.BR gh (1)
